[SN]TITLE[SN]
Margaret Evans: Alun Kinney Evans pleads guilty to killing his mother

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A man has pleaded guilty to the manslaughter of his mother in their family home in County Londonderry.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Margaret Evans, a 69-year old hairdresser who was known as Margo, was found dead in June 2014 at the house she shared with her son in Portstewart.
Alun Kinney Evans had previously denied a charge of murdering his mother.
At Antrim Crown Court, sitting in Belfast, on Tuesday, the 34-year-old admitted her manslaughter on the grounds of diminished responsibility.
Evans was remanded back into custody and is due to be sentenced on 9 June.
